The only thing saving this from being a 1 star review is that they filled my request to move to a lower room, even if it was the 2nd day of our stay.   We got there late on night one and were given a room on the 4th floor with two twin beds. I called and told them I had booked a king bed and they said "Well, you didn't, but we can move you". So they moved us to another 4th floor room that reeked of smoke and just felt old/dingy. The Internet did not work at all on the 4th floor, either. We ended up crashing on a friend's couch that night.   The next day, they moved us down to a ground floor room and the breakfast selection was decent. The new room felt, and looked, much cleaner. Also, the Internet worked. Although, the A/C wasn't great, and even though it was set at 72, we woke up sweating and had to turn it down to almost 60. The employees were polite, but many of the other guests in the lobby were incredibly rude - cutting in line, interrupting, ect.   And there was ZERO parking. We parked in the side lot for the ballrooms each night. Even though they kept telling us (and other guests) that more parking would be available. Overall, I was not impressed and would never stay here again.

